com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.configuration

Class WZStreamConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.configuration.WZMediaConfig
      • com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.configuration.WZStreamConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<WZMediaConfig>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    WowzaConfig, WZBroadcastConfig

    public class WZStreamConfig
extends WZMediaConfig
implements Serializable
    The WZStreamConfig class provides configuration properties for the streaming connection

    Usage example:

             WZStreamConfig goCoderConfig = new WZStreamConfig(FRAME_SIZE_1920x1080);
         goCoderConfig.setHostAddress("live.streamingserver.com");
         goCoderConfig.getApplicationName("LiveStreamingApp");

         goCoder.startStreaming(goCoderConfig, statusCallback);
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • setStreamMetadata

        public void setStreamMetadata(WZDataMap streamMetadata)
        The key/value pairs in the specified data map will be added to the stream metadata and accessible to Wowza Streaming Engine server modules through the onMetadata method of the IMediaStreamActionNotify2 interface. Note that non-primitive elements of type WZDataType.DATA_LIST and WZDataType.DATA_MAP will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        streamMetadata - A map of key/value pairs defining the metadata.

      • getStreamMetadata

        public WZDataMap getStreamMetadata()
        Returns:
        the current map of key/value pairs defining the metadata

      • setConnectionParameters

        public void setConnectionParameters(WZDataMap connectionParameters)
        The elements in the specified data map will be added to the connection url as query string parameters and accessible to Wowza Streaming Engine server modules through the getQueryStr method of the IClient interface. Note that WZDataType.DATE values will be serialized as an Epoch-based long value representing the number of seconds that have elapsed since January 1, 1970 and non-primitive elements of type WZDataType.DATA_LIST and WZDataType.DATA_MAP will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        connectionParameters - A map of key/value pairs defining the connection url's query string parameters. Note that elements of type WZDataType.DATA_LIST and WZDataType.DATA_MAP will be ignored
